message.content: cs.SD, cs.SD is the most likely category as the paper deals with modelling raw audio waveforms of music. cs.SD is the sub-category for Sound and Music Computing. Other likely categories could be cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing) as autoregressive models excel at generating raw audio waveforms of speech, cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper explores autoregressive discrete autoencoders (ADAs) as a means to enable autoregressive models to capture long-range correlations in waveforms, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper deals with modelling music at scale, and cs.MM (Multimedia) as the paper deals with generating piano music directly in the raw audio domain.
